    "description": "<p>\r\n\t<span style=\"color: rgb(105, 105, 105);\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\">The Association of Muslim Professionals (AMP) was established on 10 October 1991, as an important resolution of the First National Convention of Singapore Malay/Muslim Professionals which was held on 6 and 7 October 1990. The Convention was attended by 500 Malay/Muslim professionals who met to brainstorm new directions for the community. AMP was formed with core programmes in education, human resource development, social development and research.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n\t<br />\r\n\t<span style=\"color: rgb(105, 105, 105);\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: tahoma,geneva,sans-serif;\">AMP is a registered charitable organisation and is accorded the status of an Institution of Public Character.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n\t&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\t&nbsp;</p>\r\n",
